This package provides a new experimental background script console, similar to the out of box "Scripts - Background" tool provided by ServiceNow, but with the following enhancements:

*   The **Script** field provides a JavaScript editor interface instead of a plain textbox.
*   The execution results are displayed in the **Output** textarea below, allowing you to see the results on the same page; No more having to click the browser back button after every script run (and sometimes having the browser lose your script!)

**Usage**

You simply use the script editor to write your script as you normally would, then click the **Run** button above to execute the script. The results will be displayed in the **Output** field below upon completion.

**WARNING:** Any scripts run from the interface will run with the permission level of the current user (**security\_admin** if elevated, **admin** otherwise). Exercise caution in the scripts you run from this interface. All of the customary guidelines from the OOB ServiceNow background scripts page apply here as well.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Long running scripts will display a modal progress indicator until the script returns results:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Any errors in your script will be displayed via a standard ServiceNow error message dialog upon return.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**NOTE:**The tool is built using a standard SN form so the level of functionality provided by the script editor is entirely dependent on the version of ServiceNow the tool is installed on and the Script field editor capabilities associated with it. No customizations have been made to the Script field's implementation (TinyMCE as of this writing).

As this tool is a regular table form, saving scripts is allowed in the same manner as with any other table in the system. The **Name** and **Tags** fields exist to allow you to organize saved scripts.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

A journal field is also provided to allow you to keep notes on saved scripts over time.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Access**

Two new menu items are included to access the editor; both are added under the **System Definition** menu. One to access the list view of all saved scripts and the other to open a new script.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

That is basically all there is to it. It is a very simple tool which I developed during a project doing a particularly difficult integration and where lots of iterative scripted testing via background scripts was needed.

**NOTE:** This tool was developed when "Geneva" was the current platform release, and the platform has been enhanced greatly since that release and so this tool is no longer relevant in many places, but is provided for anyone who may find it useful. As with everything else on this repo, no support is provided, but feedback is welcome and I may enhance it in the future if I find a compelling reason to do so.
